{"by":"simonw","id":47779994,"parent":47778933,"text":"Re-reading Discworld books today demonstrates how timeless they are. Stories Terry wrote in the 1980s still feel like biting satire against the modern world.<p>The books also get better as I get older - I read them first as a teenager and many of the deeper ideas about the human condition went straight over my head.<p>The way the cult leader in Guards! Guards! manipulates his followers, to give just one example.","time":1776265060,"type":"comment"}